Package: perturbR
Type: Package
Title: Statistical analysis of high-throughput genetic perturbation screens
Version: 0.99.0
Date: 2018-02-1
Authors@R: person("Simon", "Dirmeier", 
	email = "simon.dirmeier@bsse.ethz.ch", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Simon Dirmeier <simon.dirmeier@bsse.ethz.ch>
Description: perturbR does statistical analysis of large-scale genetic perturbation screens.
  The package provides various tools for normalisation, plotting and analysis of 
  screens from single perturbation experiments as well as models for the joint analysis of multiple 
  experiments. For the latter case we employ a random intercepts model to capture the variance that 
  the different experiments exhibit.
